#!/bin/sh
cat <<EOF
Bash keyboard shortcuts
=======================

Characters

<C-b> move back one character
<C-f> move forward one character
<C-d> delete current character

Words

<A-b> move back one word
<A-f> move forward one word
<C-w> delete the word before the cursor
<A-d> delete the word after the cursor

Lines

<C-a> go to the beginning of the current line
<C-e> go to the end of the current line
<C-u> clear the line before the cursor
<C-k> clear the line after the cursor:

Search

<C-s> forward incremental
<C-r> backward incremental

EOF
